Author Name: **Frederic Requin**
Original Redmine Message: 1021 from https://www.veripool.org



---

Hello,

first, thanks for this wonderful tool !!
FYI, it is 40x faster than Active HDL LE.

In my simulation, I am generating VCD traces (like verybody else :-) ).
They quickly become huge over long simulation so I decided to use the openNext() method.
The problem with openNext() is that only the first segment contains and header, making others segments unreadable by regular VCD viewers.
I also tried to close() then open() another VCD file. In that case, the executable crashes when trying to create the third VCD file.
When I analyze the headers of the first two VCD files, they are not identical : it looks like new identifiers are given to the same signals.
I am wondering if the crash is due to verilator running out of identifiers.

Also, I am using time scaled VCD (to have the correct clock period in the VCD trace).
I did not find any good example so it might be useful that I post my code :
```
#include "VTop.h"
#include "verilated.h"

#if VM_TRACE
#include "verilated_vcd_c.h"
#endif

// Number of simulation cycles
#define NUM_CYCLES  ((vluint64_t)5*86000000)
// Half period (in ps) of a 27.000 MHz clock
#define HALF_PER_PS ((vluint64_t)18518)

int main(int argc, char **argv, char **env)
{
  // Half cycles
  vluint64_t hcycle;

  Verilated::commandArgs(argc, argv);
  // Init top verilog instance
  VTop* top = new VTop;

#if VM_TRACE
  // Init VCD trace dump
  Verilated::traceEverOn(true);
  VerilatedVcdC* tfp = new VerilatedVcdC;
  top->trace (tfp, 99);
  tfp->spTrace()->set_time_resolution ("1 ps");
  tfp->open ("Trace.vcd");
#endif

  // Run simulation for NUM_CYCLES clock periods
  for (hcycle = 0; hcycle < (NUM_CYCLES * 2); )
  {
     // Reset ON during 12 cycles
     top->CPU_RESET_n = (hcycle < (vluint64_t)24) ? 0 : 1;
     // Toggle clock
     top->FPGA_CLK    = top->FPGA_CLK ^ 1;
     // Evaluate verilated model
     top->eval ();

#if VM_TRACE
     // Dump signals into VCD file
     if (tfp) tfp->dump (hcycle * HALF_PER_PS);
#endif

     // Next half cycle
     hcycle++;

     if (Verilated::gotFinish())  exit(0);
  }
  top->final();

#if VM_TRACE
  if (tfp) tfp->close();
#endif

  exit(0);
}

```

Last but not least, I have created a SDR SDRAM C++ model and a VGA output C++ BMP dump class.
I think it might be useful to others.
Is there any plan to add source from contributors ?

Regards,

Frederic Requin

